==Commercial performance==

===North America===
Upon its release, "Problem" reached the top position on the [[iTunes]] singles chart in over 40 countries and the top ten in over 60 countries, including the United States, where it reached the summit in 37 minutes, hence breaking the previous record held by [[Taylor Swift]], whose single, "[[We Are Never Ever Getting Back Together]]" (2012), reached the top spot on the iTunes singles chart with a record of 37 minutes, making "Problem" the fastest selling single in digital history.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://au.ibtimes.com/articles/550009/20140429/ariana-grande-iggy-azalea-problem-featuring-yours.htm#.U2hhwWco-M8 |title=Ariana Grande's ‘Problem’ Twitter Reactions to Her New Number 1 Single - International Business Times<!-- Bot generated title --> |access-date=October 7, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140502072535/http://au.ibtimes.com/articles/550009/20140429/ariana-grande-iggy-azalea-problem-featuring-yours.htm#.U2hhwWco-M8 |archive-date=May 2, 2014 |dead-url=yes |df=mdy-all }}</ref><ref>[http://foxweekly.com/2014/05/07/now/ariana-grande-iggy-azalea-problem-to-break-record-sales.html Ariana Grande’s ‘Problem’ To Break Record Sales | Fox Weekly – Latest Breaking, U.S., World, Politics, Entertainment, Tech & Science News<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[http://www.eonline.com/news/536650/ariana-grande-s-single-problem-sets-records-singer-admits-she-likes-bad-boys-watch-now Ariana Grande's Single "Problem" Sets Records, Singer Admits She Likes Bad Boys—Watch Now!]</ref> On April 29, 2014, ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' reported that "Problem" would most likely sell more than 300,000 copies by the end of its first week of availability in the United States, as well as that the song could easily debut within the top 10 of the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] chart regardless of any added airplay or streaming points.<ref name=":0">{{cite web|last=Trust|first=Gary|title=Ariana Grande, Iggy Azalea's 'Problem' Trending Toward Huge First-Week Sales|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6070313/ariana-grande-iggy-azaleas-problem-trending-toward-huge-first-week-sales|work=Billboard}}</ref><ref name="autogenerated11">{{cite web|last=Caulfield|first=Keith|title=Ariana Grande's 'Problem' Set for Record Sales Debut|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6077517/ariana-grande-problem-record-sales-debut-hot-100-chart|work=Billboard}}</ref> In addition to its sales, which accounted for the majority of its debut chart points on the Hot 100, "Problem" began receiving early radio support. The song drew 293 first-day plays on 87 stations on the day of its release, according to Nielsen BDS. Pop Songs reporter [[KIIS-FM|KIIS Los Angeles]] led all stations with 17 first-day plays. Among all stations, "Problem" garnered 3.8 million in opening-day radio audience.<ref name=":0"/><ref name="autogenerated11" /> "Problem" officially debuted at number three on the ''Billboard'' Hot 100 chart on the week ending in May 7, 2014,<ref>{{cite web|last=Caulfield|first=Keith|title=Ariana Grande's 'Problem' Set for Record Sales Debut|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6077517/ariana-grande-problem-record-sales-debut-hot-100-chart|work=Billboard|publisher=Prometheus Global Media|date=May 5, 2014|accessdate=September 6, 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170224045633/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6077517/ariana-grande-problem-record-sales-debut-hot-100-chart|archivedate=February 24, 2017}}</ref> becoming Grande's second single to debut in the top ten, and her second top ten overall at the time, the other being "[[The Way (Ariana Grande song)|The Way]]".<ref name="autogenerated13">{{cite web|last1=Trust|first1=Gary|title=Iggy Azalea Tops Hot 100 With 'Fancy,' Matches Beatles' Historic Mark|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6099390/iggy-azalea-tops-hot-100-fancy-matches-beatles|website=Billboard|accessdate=June 14, 2014}}</ref> It became the highest debuting song of 2014 at the time, and the highest debuting song since [[Eminem]]'s "[[The Monster (song)|The Monster]]," featuring [[Rihanna]].<ref name="autogenerated13" /> "Problem" boasted just 1.3% less points than [[John Legend]]'s "[[All of Me (John Legend song)|All of Me]]", which claimed the Hot 100 top spot.<ref name="autogenerated12">[http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6077635/hot-100-john-legend-all-of-me-ariana-grande-iggy-azalea Hot 100: John Legend's "All Of Me" Hits No. 1, Ariana Grande's "Problem" Debuts At No. 3 | Billboard]</ref> In its second week, "Problem" fell one spot to number four despite gains in airplay and streaming, while Iggy Azalea's "[[Fancy (Iggy Azalea song)|Fancy]]" replaced it as number three.<ref name="autogenerated12" /> "Problem" returned to its number three peak the following week before moving to a new peak at number two in its fourth week on the chart; Azalea's "Fancy" moved to the top of both the Digital and Hot 100 charts, boasting 28% more overall chart points than "Problem".<ref name="autogenerated13"/><ref name="sold">{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6092276/michael-jackson-coldplay-hot-100-top-10-john-legend-no-1?mobile_redirection=false|first=Gary|last=Trust|title=Michael Jackson, Coldplay Hit Hot 100's Top 10; John Legend Still No. 1|accessdate=May 22, 2014}}</ref> "Problem" remained in the runner-up spot the following week, holding that position for five consecutive weeks.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Trust|first1=Gary|title=Ariana Grande, Iggy Azalea Triple Up in Hot 100's Top 10, MAGIC! Still No. 1|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6221978/hot-100-ariana-grande-iggy-azalea-top-10-magic|work=Billboard|accessdate=August 20, 2014}}</ref> The song stayed in the [[Hot 100]]'s top 10 for the first 16 weeks of its chart run, making its number three debut on May 7, 2014 and dropping out of the top 10 on August 27, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Trust|first1=Gary|title=John Legend's 'All of Me' Tops Hot 100, Ariana Grande Debuts at No. 3|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6077635/hot-100-john-legend-all-of-me-ariana-grande-iggy-azalea|work=Billboard|accessdate=May 7, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Grein|first1=Paul|title=Chart Watch: Nicki Minaj Zooms To #2|url=https://music.yahoo.com/blogs/chart-watch/chart-watch-nicki-minaj-zooms-to-2-221739201.html|publisher=Yahoo!|accessdate=August 27, 2014}}</ref>

On [[Mainstream Top 40|''Billboard'' Pop Songs]], the song debuted at number 28 and reached number 21 in its second week on the chart.<ref name = "top40pop"/> It debuted at number 24 on [[Rhythmic (chart)|''Billboard'' Rhythmic Songs]] chart, it moved up eight places to number 16 in its second week on the chart and peaked at number one.<ref name = "rhythmic"/> It eventually reached number one on both the Billboard Pop Songs and Rhythmic Songs charts, becoming Grande's first number one single on both charts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6141124/ariana-grande-iggy-azalea-top-pop-rhythmic-songs-charts-with|title=Ariana Grande, Iggy Azalea Top Pop, Rhythmic Songs Charts With 'Problem'|date=June 30, 2014|accessdate=April 16, 2015}}</ref> "Problem" just missed the entry into the ''[[Hot 100 Airplay (Radio Songs)|Billboard]]'' [[Hot 100 Airplay (Radio Songs)|Radio Songs]] chart in its first week of availability. It officially entered in at number 30 on the chart, up 70% in audience impressions from 24 million to 41 million.<ref name="autogenerated12" /><ref name="autogenerated20">{{cite web|last1=Trust|first1=Gary|title=John Legend Leads Hot 100, Paramore Hits Top|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6084939/john-legend-hot-100-chart-paramore-top-10|website=Billboard|accessdate=June 14, 2014}}</ref> It rocketed 14 spots to number 16 in its second week, granting it the Hot 100's top Airplay Gainer award.<ref name="sold"/> It reached the top 10 of the Radio Songs chart at number 10 in its third week on the chart, up 30% in audience impressions from 56 million to 73 million. The song reached a peak of Number 2 in its 7th week and remained there for 3 weeks.<ref name="autogenerated13"/> In addition to this, the track also debuted on the [[Streaming Songs]] chart at number nine in its first week and moved five spots to number four in its second week, with a weekly peak of 4.4 million and 6.5 million, respectively.<ref name="autogenerated12" /><ref name="autogenerated20" /> It has since peaked at number two in its third week on the chart.<ref name="sold"/>

"Problem" debuted atop the [[Digital Songs|''Billboard'' Hot Digital Songs]] chart at number one, selling 438,000 copies in its opening week, thus earning Grande the highest first-week sales numbers of 2014 at the time and also her biggest digital song sales week ever, breaking her previous record held by "[[The Way (Ariana Grande song)|The Way]]", which sold 219,000 digital copies for the week ending April 5, 2013.<ref name="autogenerated12" /> It is Grande's first number one single on that chart. It is the overall 9th biggest debut for a digital song and is the 5th largest by a female artist, behind [[Taylor Swift]]'s "[[We Are Never Ever Getting Back Together]]" (2012), [[Katy Perry]]'s "[[Roar (song)|Roar]]" (2013), Swift's "[[Shake It Off (Taylor Swift song)|Shake It Off]]" (2014) and [[Lady Gaga]]'s "[[Born This Way (song)|Born This Way]]" (2011).<ref>{{cite web|last1=Caulfield|first1=Keith|title='Frozen' Spends Lucky 13th Week at No. 1, Lindsey Stirling Bows at No. 2|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6077608/frozen-spends-lucky-13th-week-at-no-1-lindsey-stirling-bows-at-no-2|website=Billboard|accessdate=June 14, 2014}}</ref> Further, at 20 years old, Grande became the youngest woman to debut with more than 400,000 downloads.<ref name="autogenerated11"/> "Problem" also became the highest debut for a collaboration of only female soloists since "[[Give Me All Your Luvin']]" by [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna]], [[Nicki Minaj]] and [[M.I.A. (rapper)|M.I.A.]] debuted at number 13 on the chart following Madonna's [[List of Super Bowl halftime shows|Super Bowl XLVI Halftime Show]] performance in February 2012.<ref name="autogenerated13" /> "Problem" spent a second week at number one on the Digital Songs chart with an additional 235,000 units sold, despite a 46% drop.<ref name="autogenerated20" /> The song topped the chart again in its third week selling 248,000 units, before slipping one spot to number two in its fourth week on the chart, despite a 15% growth of 284,000 units.<ref name="sold"/> The song reached its first million sales mark in the United States on May 28, 2014.<ref>{{citation |url=https://music.yahoo.com/blogs/chart-watch/chart-watch-meet-iggy-azalea-211310608.html |title=Chart Watch: Meet Iggy Azalea! |author= Paul Grein |date=May 28, 2014 |work=Yahoo Chart Watch }}</ref> On May 29, 2014, it was certified [[RIAA certification|platinum]] by the [[Recording Industry Association of America]], becoming Grande's second song to be certified platinum.{{Certification Cite Ref|region=United States|title=Problem|artist=Ariana Grande|type=single|certyear=2014}} As of April 2018, "Problem" has sold 3.7 million copies in the United States.<ref name="us_sales">{{Cite magazine |last=Trust |first=Gary |date=April 22, 2018 |title=Ask Billboard: Ariana Grande's Career Album & Song Sales |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/8363518/ariana-grande-career-album-song-sales-ask-billboard |magazine=Billboard |access-date=April 22, 2018}}</ref>

In Canada, "Problem" debuted at number three on the [[Canadian Hot 100]] on May 17, 2014, becoming her first top 10 single in that country.<ref>{{cite web|title=Billboard Canadian Hot 100 for the Week of May 17, 2014|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/2014-05-17/canadian-hot-100|website=Billboard|accessdate=June 14, 2014}}</ref> In its second week on the chart the song dropped 12 places to number 15.<ref>{{cite web|title=Billboard Canadian Hot 100 for the Week of May 24, 2014|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/2014-05-24/canadian-hot-100|website=Billboard|accessdate=June 14, 2014}}</ref> In its 3rd week the song rose back to the top 10 at number six.<ref>{{cite web|title=Billboard Canadian Hot 100 for the Week of May 31, 2014|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/2014-05-31/canadian-hot-100|website=Billboard|accessdate=June 14, 2014}}</ref> In its fourth week the song rose even higher to number 4.<ref>{{cite web|title=Billboard Canadian Hot 100 for the Week of June 7, 2014|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/2014-06-07/canadian-hot-100|website=Billboard|accessdate=June 14, 2014}}</ref>  "Problem" was the first song to top the weekly [[Billboard Twitter Real-Time|''Billboard'' Twitter Top Tracks]] chart on June 12, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Gruger|first1=William|title=Ariana Grande, Iggy Azalea Dominate Billboard's Twitter & Social Charts|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6113711/twitter-social-charts-ariana-grande-iggy-azalea|website=Billboard|accessdate=June 14, 2014}}</ref>

===Europe and Oceania===
In the United Kingdom, "Problem" debuted at number one on the [[UK Singles Chart]] on July 6, 2014 ― for the week ending date July 12, 2014 ― becoming Grande's fourth charting single and first chart-topper in Britain and Azalea's seventh and first respectively. According to the [[Official Charts Company]], "Problem" made British chart history upon its debut as the first song to top the charts in Britain based on both sales and streaming, with a combined 'chart sales' figure of 113,000.<ref>Lane, Dan (July 6, 2014). [http://www.officialcharts.com/chart-news/ariana-grande-earns-a-place-in-official-chart-history-with-problem-3146/ "Ariana Grande earns a place in Official Chart history with Problem"]. ''Official Charts''. Retrieved November 23, 2015.</ref> In the Belgian [[Ultratop|Ultratop 50]], "Problem" peaked at number 26 in [[Flanders]] and number 40 in [[Wallonia]].<ref name="fln"/><ref name="wln"/> It also debuted at number 22 in Switzerland, becoming Grande's first charting single in that country.<ref name="swi"/> It also appeared in Netherlands at number 10,<ref name="dut100" /> in Spain at number 11,<ref name="spa" /> in Austria at number 31, in Germany at number 25 and in Brazil at number 87.<ref name="aut" /><ref name="bra" />

In New Zealand, "Problem" made its first chart appearance on the [[New Zealand Singles Chart]] on the issue dated May 5, 2014. It debuted at the number-one spot on the chart, becoming the highest debut of the week, making it Grande's first single to top the charts in New Zealand, first top debut and her second top forty single.<ref name="NZdebut">{{cite web |url=http://nztop40.co.nz/chart/singles?chart=2493 |title=NZ Top 40 Singles Chart |publisher=[[Recorded Music NZ]] |date=May 5, 2014 |accessdate=May 2, 2014}}</ref> In its second week on the chart, the song dropped two spots to number three being replaced by the songs featured artist [[Iggy Azalea]], whose single "[[Fancy (Iggy Azalea song)|Fancy]]" featuring [[Charli XCX]] took over the top spot.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://nztop40.co.nz/chart/singles?chart=2497 |title=NZ Top 40 Singles Chart |publisher=[[Recorded Music NZ]] |date=May 12, 2014 |accessdate=June 14, 2014}}</ref><ref name="Problem6AUS">{{cite web|last=Ryan|first=Gavin|title=Justice Crew Hold Onto The Top Spot on the ARIA Singles Chart|url=http://www.ariacharts.com.au/news/46307/justice-crew-hold-the-top-spot-on-the-aria-singles-chart?pos=0|work=ARIA Charts|accessdate=May 17, 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140518002302/http://www.ariacharts.com.au/news/46307/justice-crew-hold-the-top-spot-on-the-aria-singles-chart?pos=0|archivedate=May 18, 2014|df=mdy-all}}</ref>
In Azalea's native Australia, "Problem" gave Grande her first top 10 hit after it debuted at number four on the [[Australian Singles Chart]],<ref name="AUSdebut">{{cite web |url=http://www.ariacharts.com.au/news/46125/ed-sheeran-%27sing%27-is-no.1-on-the-aria-singles-chart! |title=ARIA Singles Chart |publisher=[[ARIA Charts|ARIA Singles Chart]] |date=May 5, 2014 |accessdate=May 2, 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140503192435/http://ariacharts.com.au/news/46125/ed-sheeran-'sing'-is-no.1-on-the-aria-singles-chart! |archive-date=May 3, 2014 |dead-url=yes }}</ref> and eventually ascended to number two in its second week on the chart.<ref name="aus" /> It stayed in the top two for two consecutive weeks, Grande's previous best effort on the chart was "[[The Way (Ariana Grande song)|The Way]]" which peaked at number 37 in April 2013 and also became her second top 40 effort there.<ref name="aus" /><ref name="Problem6AUS"/><ref name="AUSdebut" /> According to the [[International Federation of the Phonographic Industry]] (IFPI), "Problem" has achieved global sales of 9 millions of units (combined sales plus streaming data) as of 2015, ranking as the eighth best-selling single of 2014 and making it one of the [[best-selling singles worldwide]].<ref name=worldwidesalesifpi>{{cite web|title=IFPI Digital Music Report 2015 - Global top 10 digital singles 2014|url=http://www.ifpi.org/news/Global-digital-music-revenues-match-physical-format-sales-for-first-time|publisher=[[IFPI]]|accessdate=April 14, 2015}}</ref>

==Music video==

===Lyric video===
Grande and Iggy Azalea filmed the [[lyric video]] for "Problem" on April 10, 2014 with Jones Crow as the director.<ref>[https://twitter.com/ArianaGrande/status/454175699071270912 Twitter / ArianaGrande: shot a lyric video for my first]</ref> Grande assisted Crow in editing the video and completed it on April 13, 2014<ref>[https://twitter.com/ArianaGrande/status/455473052420022273 Twitter / ArianaGrande: lyric video done, song is mixed<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> and it premiered on [[Vevo]] on May 30, 2014. The video features Grande and Azalea performing in a [[Film noir|noir]] black-and-white clip behind [[Pinwheel (toy)|pinwheel]] go-go filters.<ref name=autogenerated14/><ref>{{cite web|last1=Williott|first1=Carl|title=Ariana Grande & Iggy Azalea's "Problem" Lyric Video: Watch|url=http://www.idolator.com/7516323/ariana-grande-iggy-azalea-problem-lyric-video|website=Idolator|accessdate=June 14, 2014}}</ref>

===Official music video===
[[File:Ariana Grande - Problem (Screenshot).jpg|thumb|right|250px|Grande and Azalea in a colorful backdrop during the music video which incorporates elements from 1960s art.]]
The official music video was filmed on April 29, 2014, just one day after the single's release, and was directed by The Young Astronauts who had previously worked with Grande on videos for her singles "[[Right There (Ariana Grande song)|Right There]]" and "[[Almost Is Never Enough]]". [[Big Sean]] makes an appearance in the video.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ariana Grande And Big Sean Film "Problem" Music Video|url=http://www.disneydreaming.com/2014/04/30/ariana-grande-and-big-sean-film-problem-video/|website=Disney Dreaming|accessdate=June 14, 2014}}</ref> The video was set with a [[retro style]] from [[1960s in Western fashion|1960s]] [[art movement]] containing a black, white, and old-fashioned aesthetic.<ref>{{cite web|title=First Look: Ariana Grande And Iggy Azalea Go Mod In 'Problem' Video|url=http://www.rap-up.com/2014/05/08/first-look-ariana-grande-and-iggy-azalea-go-mod-in-problem-video/|website=Rap-Up|accessdate=June 14, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Garibaldi|first1=Christina|title=Ariana Grande And Iggy Azalea Tease Their Hair And Their 'Problem' Video|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1822422/ariana-grande-and-iggy-azalea-tease-their-hair-and-their-problem-video/|publisher=MTV|accessdate=June 14, 2014}}</ref> The video opens on a sparkling figure where Grande appears in a sequined [[minidress]] and white [[go go boots]] with her dancers backed by a spiral backdrop. Iggy Azalea is shown in front of a colorful background, and, as Jason Lipzshuts from ''Billboord'' noted, her hairstyle is reminiscent of ''[[Barbarella (film)|Barbarella]]'',<ref name="BillbVideo">{{cite magazine|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop-shop/6106283/ariana-grande-problem-music-video-iggy-azalea-big-sean|title= Ariana Grande's 'Problem' Video: Watch Ariana & Iggy Azalea Turn Back Time|magazine= Billboard|date= May 30, 2014|access-date= July 3, 2017}}</ref> while Chima Simone of ''[[E!]]'' compared her hair to [[Nancy Sinatra]]'s in her "[[These Boots Are Made for Walkin']]" (1966) video.<ref name="e!">{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/547111/ariana-grande-drops-problem-video-featuring-iggy-azalea-and-big-sean-watch-now|title= Ariana Grande Drops "Problem" Video Featuring Iggy Azalea and Big Sean: Watch Now!|publisher= [[E!]]|date= May 30, 2014|access-date= July 3, 2017}}</ref> The video contains intercepted scenes of Grande lying atop a giant spiral on a pink floor wearing an white [[sweater]] and high socks. Lia Ben from website [[Bustle (magazine)|Bustle]] compared the scene to [[Britney Spears]]'s "[[Oops!... I Did It Again (song)|Oops!... I Did It Again]] music video (2000).<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://www.bustle.com/articles/26405-ariana-grande-iggy-azaleas-problem-music-video-is-just-as-addictive-as-the-song|title=Ariana Grande & Iggy Azalea's "Problem" Music Video Is Just as Addictive as the Song — VIDEO|magazine= [[Bustle]]|date= May 30, 2014|access-date= July 3, 2017}}</ref>

===Accolades===
The video was released on May 30, 2014, and it surpassed 100 million views on July 28, consequently making it Grande's second Vevo-certified music video after "[[The Way (Ariana Grande song)|The Way]]".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://arianatoday.net/archives/3269|title=Ariana Grande's 'Problem' is #VEVOCERTIFIED|accessdate=November 14, 2015}}</ref> As of September 2018, the music video has over 1.1 billion views on [[YouTube]].<ref name="youtube">{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iS1g8G_njx8|title=Ariana Grande – Problem ft. Iggy Azalea |publisher=[[YouTube]]|author=ArianaGrandeVevo|accessdate=February 23, 2015}}</ref> The lyric video was nominated at the [[2014 MTV Video Music Awards]] in the Best Lyric Video category.<ref>{{cite web|title=best lyric video|url=http://www.mtv.com/ontv/vma/2014/best-lyric-video/|publisher=MTV|accessdate=August 26, 2014}}</ref> The official music video was nominated in the Best Collaboration, Best Female Video, and Best Pop Video categories, and it ultimately won the award for Best Pop Video.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Kaufman|first1=Gil|title=2014 MTV Video Music Awards Nominations: Get The Full List|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1870248/2014-video-music-awards-nominations-full-list/|publisher=MTV|accessdate=July 17, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=winners|url=http://www.mtv.com/ontv/vma/2014/winners.jhtml|publisher=MTV|accessdate=August 26, 2014}}</ref> It was Grande's and Azalea's first time winning a [[MTV Video Music Award|VMA]].<ref name="mtv.com">{{cite web|last1=Ehrlich|first1=Brenna|title=Ponytail Princess Ariana Grande Wins Best Pop Video VMA|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/1909975/ariana-grande-best-pop-video-vma/|publisher=MTV|accessdate=August 24, 2014}}</ref>

==Live performances==
"Problem" was first performed by Grande at the [[2014 Radio Disney Music Awards]] on April 26, 2014, which were aired a day later on April 27, 2014.<ref name="autogenerated6"/><ref name="idolator">{{cite web |url=http://www.idolator.com/7515862/ariana-grande-problem-performance-radio-disney-music-awards |title=Ariana Grande Debuts "Problem" With Sexy Radio Disney Music Awards Performance: Watch |publisher=Idolator.com |accessdate=April 29, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Benjamin|first=Jeff|title=Ariana Grande Premiers New Single "Problem" At Radio Disney Music Awards|url=http://www.fuse.tv/2014/04/ariana-grande-problem-iggy-azalea|work=[[Fuse.tv]]|accessdate=April 28, 2014}}</ref> It was later performed at Jeffrey Sanker's annual [[White Party]] in Palm Springs.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Pilcher|first1=Rachel|title=ARIANA GRANDE DRESSES AS A RETRO BABY SPICE FOR PERFORMANCE AT 'WHITE PARTY' – PICS|url=http://www.sugarscape.com/main-topics/fashion-beauty/1035773/ariana-grande-dresses-retro-baby-spice-performance-white-party-pi|website=SugarScape|accessdate=June 14, 2014}}</ref> Grande has since also performed "Problem" at the [[2014 iHeartRadio Music Awards]] on May 1, 2014,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://arianatoday.net/archives/2570 |title=Ariana Grande to perform at the 2014 Radio Music Awards |publisher=Ariana Today |accessdate=April 22, 2014}}</ref> on ''[[The Ellen DeGeneres Show]]'' on May 6, 2014,<ref>{{cite web|title=ARIANA GRANDE PERFORMS 'PROBLEM' ON 'ELLEN'|url=http://www.rap-up.com/2014/05/06/ariana-grande-performs-problem-on-ellen/#more-185273|website=Rap-Up|accessdate=June 14, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Ortiz|first1=edwin|title=Watch Ariana Grande Perform "Problem" on "Ellen"|url=http://www.complex.com/music/2014/05/ariana-grande-performs-problem-on-ellen|website=Complex Music|accessdate=June 14, 2014}}</ref> and at the Born Free Africa Mother's Day Family Carnival on May 11.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ariana Grande Performance (Problem) on Mothers Day at Born Free Africa|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=P-7pPLoAW_I|publisher=YouTube}}</ref> Grande has also performed the song at various concerts including the 2014 [[KIIS-FM]]'s 102.7 [[Wango Tango]] annual concert alongside Azalea, for the first time performed with her on May 10,<ref>{{cite web|title=ARIANA GRANDE AND IGGY AZALEA PERFORM 'PROBLEM' AT WANGO TANGO|url=http://www.rap-up.com/2014/05/11/ariana-grande-and-iggy-azalea-perform-problem-at-wango-tango/|publisher=Rap-Up.com|accessdate=May 11, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Ariana Grande Added To Wango Tango Concert Lineup|url=http://www.disneydreaming.com/2014/05/02/ariana-grande-added-to-wango-tango-concert-lineup/|website=Disney Dreaming|accessdate=June 14, 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141011221449/http://www.disneydreaming.com/2014/05/02/ariana-grande-added-to-wango-tango-concert-lineup/|archive-date=October 11, 2014|dead-url=yes}}</ref> the annual [[WXKS-FM|Kiss 108 fm]]'s 2014 Kiss Concert on May 31, 2014 and at the 2014 New York [[WKTU|103.5 KTU]] concert KTUphoria on June 29, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|title=That's a Wrap on Kiss Concert|url=http://www.kiss108.com/pages/KC2014/|publisher=KISS108.com|accessdate=June 14, 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140530024822/http://www.kiss108.com/pages/KC2014/|archivedate=May 30, 2014|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=2014 #KTUphoria Artist Lineup|url=http://www.ktu.com/pages/events/ktuphoria/2014/|publisher=KTU.com|accessdate=June 14, 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140626075226/http://www.ktu.com/pages/events/ktuphoria/2014/|archivedate=June 26, 2014|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Grande performed the song at the [[2014 Billboard Music Awards]] alongside Azalea on May 18, 2014. Later, Grande performed on the [[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. season 18)|season 18]] finale of ''[[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. TV series)|Dancing with the Stars]]'' on May 20, 2014<ref>{{cite web|title=Ariana Grande, Iggy Azalea to Perform on 2014 Billboard Music Awards|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/events/bbma-2014/6084776/ariana-grande-iggy-azalea-performers-billboard-music-awards|work=Billboard|accessdate=May 13, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Lee|first=Christina|title=Ariana Grande, Iggy Azalea & Cody Simpson Perform At 'Dancing with the Stars' Finale|url=http://www.idolator.com/7519295/ariana-grande-problem-dwts-finale|publisher=SpinMedia|accessdate=May 22, 2014}}</ref> and at the [[2014 MuchMusic Video Awards]] on June 15.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Longeretta|first1=Emily|title=Ariana Grande Closes MMVAs With Sexy Performance Of 'Problem'|url=http://hollywoodlife.com/2014/06/15/ariana-grande-performance-muchmusic-video-awards-2014-problem/|website=Hollywood Life|accessdate=June 16, 2014}}</ref> She performed "Problem" at the 2014 iHeartRadio Ultimate Pool Party, and a piano version on the one-day revival of [[Total Request Live]]. On August 28, Grande performed the song at the program [[Today (U.S. TV program)|Today Show]] and also during a pocket show held at the Honda Stage at the iHeartRadio Theatre in LA. She also performed "Problem" along with "[[Bang Bang (Jessie J, Ariana Grande and Nicki Minaj song)|Bang Bang]]" and "[[Break Free (song)|Break Free]]" on ''[[The X Factor (Australia series 6)|The X Factor Australia]]'' on September 8, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://au.tv.yahoo.com/x-factor/24905001/latest-and-greatest-special-guests/|title=Latest and Greatest: Special Guests|work=The X Factor Australia|publisher=Yahoo!7|date=September 5, 2014|accessdate=September 8, 2014|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140908204408/https://au.tv.yahoo.com/x-factor/24905001/latest-and-greatest-special-guests/|archivedate=September 8, 2014|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Still on September 8, Ariana performed the song at the Australian TV Show ''[[Sunrise (Australian TV program)|Sunrise]]'' along with Break Free. On September 12 she performed a medley version of Problem and Break Free in the Japanese TV Show [[Music Station]]. She also performed "Problem" at the [[iHeartRadio Music Festival]] on September 19, 2014. Ariana performed the song along with "Break Free" at the [[2014 MTV Europe Music Awards]] on November 9, 2014. Ariana performed the song along with "Break Free" and "[[Love Me Harder]]" at the [[American Music Awards of 2014|American Music Awards]] on November 23, 2014.<ref>[http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6319948/ariana-grande-will-perform-at-2014-american-music-awards "Ariana Grande Will Perform at 2014 American Music Awards"]. ''[[Billboard (magazine)]]'' (November 19, 2014). Retrieved November 23, 2015. {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141119014356/http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6319948/ariana-grande-will-perform-at-2014-american-music-awards |date=November 19, 2014 }}</ref>

==Cover versions==
In July the same year English band [[Rixton (band)|Rixton]] released a cover of "Problem". [[Idolator (website)|Idolator]] wrote they "replaced the brass-heavy original with soulful harmonies, snaps and nasty guitar licks. No Iggy section to be found here, but with lead singer Jake's powerful chops at the forefront, the rap is hardly missed."<ref>{{cite web|last1=Stern|first1=Bradley|title=Rixton Cover Ariana Grande's "Problem": Watch|url=http://www.idolator.com/7526079/rixton-covers-ariana-grande-problem-watch|website=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|accessdate=August 18, 2014|date=July 10, 2014}}</ref> The a cappella group [[Pentatonix]] covered the song on their album ''PTX Vol. 3'', released on September 23, 2014.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Papadatos|first1=Markos|title=Pentatonix to release first single and video from 'PTX Vol. 3'|url=http://www.digitaljournal.com/a-and-e/music/pentatonix-to-release-first-single-and-video-from-ptx-vol-3/article/396697|website=Digital Journal|accessdate=August 18, 2014|date=August 13, 2014}}</ref> ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' noted the cover was more "low-key" than the original version.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Snetiker|first1=Marc|title=Pentatonix drops the sax to cover Ariana Grande and Iggy Azalea's 'Problem'|url=http://music-mix.ew.com/2014/08/12/pentatonix-ariana-grande-problem/|website=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|accessdate=August 12, 2014|date=August 18, 2014}}</ref> ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' said it was "catchy".<ref>{{cite web|last1=Strecker|first1=Erin|title=Watch Pentatonix Cover Ariana Grande's 'Problem'|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6214453/pentatonix-problem-ariana-grande-cover|website=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=August 18, 2014|date=August 12, 2014}}</ref>

