==Credits and personnel==
Credits adapted from ''My Everything'' liner notes.<ref name="Album Credits">{{cite AV media notes |title=My Everything |others=[[Ariana Grande]] |year=2014 |type=CD |publisher=[[Republic Records]] |id=3799485 |page=1–2}}</ref>

;Recording
* Recorded at [[Conway Recording Studios]] ([[Los Angeles]], [[California]]) and [[Wolf Cousins Studio]] ([[Stockholm]], [[Sweden]])
* Mixed at MixStar Studios ([[Virginia Beach]], [[Virginia]])
* Mastered at Sterling Sound ([[New York City]], [[New York (state)|New York]])

;Management
* Wolf Cousins ([[STIM]]), Warner Chappell Music Scandinavia, AB (STIM), MXM (administered by Kobalt), Grand Hustle Publishing, Grandarimusic Publishing ([[American Society of Composers, Authors and Publishers|ASCAP]]), MXM (administered by Kobalt) (ASCAP)
* [[Iggy Azalea]] appears courtesy of [[Virgin EMI Records]], under exclusive license in the United States to [[Def Jam Recordings]]
* [[Big Sean]] appears courtesy of Def Jam Recordings

;Personnel
{{div col|colwidth=30em}}
* [[Ariana Grande]]&nbsp;– songwriting, lead vocals
* [[Iggy Azalea]]&nbsp;– songwriting, featured artist
* [[Big Sean]]&nbsp;– background vocals
* [[Max Martin]]&nbsp;– songwriting, production for MXM Productions, vocal production, keys, programming
* [[Ilya Salmanzadeh|Ilya]]&nbsp;– songwriting, production for Wolf Cousins Productions, guitar, bass, keys, programming, background vocals
* [[Savan Kotecha]]&nbsp;– songwriting, background vocals
* [[Shellback (record producer)|Shellback]]&nbsp;– production for Wolf Cousins Productions, keys, programming
* [[Carolina Liar|Peter Carlsson]]&nbsp;– vocal production, engineering
* Sam Holland&nbsp;– engineering
* Serban Ghenea&nbsp;– mixing
* John Hanes&nbsp;– mixing engineering
* Tom Coyne&nbsp;– mastering
* Aya Merrill&nbsp;– mastering
* Leon Silva&nbsp;– saxophone
